Infos.Info:
Let's consider one of the loop construction options - <color=green>for loop</color>. It can be used in situations where the number of iterations (loop repetitions) is known before entering the loop. It has the following form:
for (<initialization>; <condition>; <execution order>) 
{
<actions>
}
<color=green>Initialization</color> — setting the initial parameters of the counter;
<color=green> Condition</color> is a condition for exiting the loop, as soon as it returns false, the loop will exit;
<color=green>Execution order</color> is a command to increase the counter.
Actions performed cyclically are called the loop body .

Now let's move on to another version of the loop construction - <color=green>while loop</color>. In this case, the actions of the loop are repeated until the specified condition is met. This loop functions according to the principle: First, we think after doing. In general, it looks like this:
 while(<Condition>)
 {
 <Actions>
 }
